nl_problem:
# Task: Nested Logic Test (Depth 10)
# Interface:
Class: Solution
Method: checkNested(self, x0: int, x1: int, x2: int, x3: int, x4: int, x5: int, x6: int, x7: int, x8: int, x9: int) -> bool

# Objective:
This is a test of structural nesting. Return True ONLY if all the following conditions are met:
1. x0 is greater than 0
2. x1 is greater than 0
3. x2 is greater than 0
4. x3 is greater than 0
5. x4 is greater than 0
6. x5 is greater than 0
7. x6 is greater than 0
8. x7 is greater than 0
9. x8 is greater than 0
10. x9 is greater than 0

Each condition must be checked inside the previous one (nested if statements).
lisp_spec:
(task
  (name "checkNested")
  (signature ((x0 int) (x1 int) (x2 int) (x3 int) (x4 int) (x5 int) (x6 int) (x7 int) (x8 int) (x9 int)) bool
  (constraints
    (constraint "All input parameters must be integers.")
    (constraint "The number of input parameters is fixed at 10.")
    (constraint "Each parameter x0 to x9 must be greater than 0.")
  )
  (goal
    (description "Check if all the given integer inputs are greater than 0 using nested conditions.")
    (rule "Start by checking if x0 is greater than 0. If true, proceed to check x1; otherwise return False.")
    (rule "If x1 is also greater than 0, continue to check x2; otherwise, return False.")
    (rule "Continue this pattern for all parameters up to x9.")
    (return "Return True if all input parameters are greater than 0. Otherwise, return False.")
  )
)
